This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it deals with replicated data types that can be modified without coordination between replicas. It could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it discusses the properties of a specific type of data structure. Additionally, it could be categorized under Databases (cs.DB) as it deals with data replication. Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) are also possible sub-categories as they both deal with the design and implementation of software systems, which is relevant to the development of CRDTs.
